JOHANNESBURG - Mining company Rio Tinto and two of its former executives will face a court challenge in Australia. This follows allegations the miner misled investors about coal reserves in a Mozambican acquisition. The Australian Securities and Investments Commission alleges Rio Tinto published false statements in a 2011 company annual report. READ:Â How Steinhoff execs cooked the books The company previously denied any wrongdoing in a similar case brought by the US Securities and Exchange Commission. The Australian watchdog wants the court to find Rio Tinto in contempt of the Corporations Act. It also wants the company to pay a fine. eNCA